Text.string: Hi!
Hello there.
Oh, wow. Hi!
Hey there, Vault Hunter!
What's happenin'?
How's your day been?
Nice day! Except for... everything.
Evening!
You're up late.
My world's a warzone, and I've eaten ratch twice this week, but I'm staying positive!
I just gotta keep a smile on my face and a target off my back!
A friggin' psycho nearly took my head off the other day. Thankfully, Lorelei saved me. She's pretty badass, huh?
Looks like Atlas could use all the help they can get.
Why couldn't Maliwan just leave us alone? They didn't have to do all this.
Bandits poppin' up out of thin air. What fresh hell will we have to deal with next?
I heard Tyreen sucks people's souls out. Is that true?
Haven't seen my family since the invasion. It's awesome!
I'm taking this invasion as a sign, you know? New war, new me!
Have you seen the Calypsos' ECHOcasts? They're friggin' insane.||—But I can't stop watching them.
Thanks for your help with Promethea. We were barely scrapin' by before you showed up.
You should see what the Calypso Twins say about you on their ECHOcasts. It's pretty brutal.
I know I shouldn't watch the Calypsos' ECHOcasts, but it's like watching a car crash. You can't look away or you'll miss it!
We're so glad the Crimson Raiders showed up when they did.
Any jobs I could take care of on this space ship?
We're in space, Vault Hunter! Spaaaace!
Have you seen the view out there? It's friggin' magical!
Thanks for helping out Atlas down there on Promethea. It means a lot to us.
Vault Hunters and spaceships—my life's gotten pretty exciting lately.
[yawns]
[yawns]
[yawns]
[yawns]
[yawns]
[yawns]
Bye then!
See you around!
Don't get shot!
Stay safe!||—That's a... dumb thing to say.
See you, Vault Hunter!
See you on the other side of the war!
When the war's over, let's get dinner!
I believe in you!
Thanks for everything!
Come back, okay?
Trying to remember if I've looted the pharmacy on DeVega street already...
I would kill someone for a cheeseburger right now.
I know everyone's talking about it, but for the record, I think Rhys's mustache looks great.
I guess we just have to trust that Atlas can get the city working again.
Living under Maliwan occupation was no fun, believe me.
Damn those corporations! They don't care who they step on to get what they want. Good thing Atlas is different now.
I wanted to get out there and kick some Maliwan ass myself, but they've got all this fancy gear and training and everything.
I am never buying a Maliwan product again! Might steal one, though.
I miss pizza and running water and being mad about celebrity affairs.
That tagline “like, follow, and obey” makes my skin crawl every time.
Yeah, I've killed a few bandits. You gotta do what you gotta do.
I bet Lorelei would make a good Vault Hunter, don't you?
It's so scary to think about how many bandit lunatics hang on Tyreen's every word.
You think Promethea will ever get back to normal?
Feelin' it!
Get hype!
This is neat!
Make some noise!
I'm makin' friends!
Keep it positive!
Sending good thoughts your way!
Aw, that's art right there!
[burp] Ratch burgers, man...
[burp] Ah, there it is.
[burp] Thought gravity would keep that down.
Greetings!
Salutations!
Wanna see my bucket of ears?
“Pip pip!” Learned that from Lorelei.
Keepin' it real!
Got a locker full of jabber toes if you're interested! Please be interested.
